<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thisdayonline.com/nview.php?id=105443|title=\u2018Declare Onikan a Disaster Zone\u2019}}</ref> They played the first part of the 2008\u201309 season in [[Isoko South|Oleh]] because of renovations to the Warri Stadium.<ref>[http://www.guardiannewsngr.com/sports/article14//indexn3_html?pdate=080908&ptitle=Wolves%20set%20for%20Glo%20League%20opener%20against%20Gateway&cpdate=080908 Nigeria needs 100,000 mw to meet demand, says expert]</ref>\nThe Seasiders as they are fondly called are back in Warri City. They now play all their matches at the Warri Township Stadium.\n\n==Performance in CAF competitions==\n*'''[[CAF Champions League]]: 1 appearance'''\n::[[CAF Champions League 2016|2016]]&nbsp;\u2013 First Round\n\n*'''[[CAF Confederation Cup]]: 3 appearances'''\n::[[CAF Confederation Cup 2010|2010]]&nbsp;\u2013 First Round of 16\n::[[2012 CAF Confederation Cup|2012]]&nbsp;\u2013 Second Round\n::[[2014 CAF Confederation Cup|2014]]&nbsp;\u2013 Second Round\n\n*'''[[CAF Cup]]: 1 appearance'''\n::2002&nbsp;\u2013 First Round (as NPA)\n\n==Staff==\n* Peter Nieketien (Technical Adviser)\n* Moses Etu (Chairman)\n* Azuka Chiemeka (Media Officer)\n* Tony Okowa (Chairman of Delta Sports Commission)\n* Ogenyi Evans (Head Coach)\n\n==Current 2019/2020 Squad==\n* Walter Ighoakpokire\n* Dikoo Mayoo\n* Okoyoh Michael\n* Abu Azeez\n* Omoduemake Moses\n* Atsimene Charles\n* Mamadu Belema\n* Isaec Ogiogio\n* Iteji Jimmy\n* Mark Daniel\n* Egbeta Michael\n* Innocent Orukpe\n* Yarhere Efe\n* Makalala Victor\n* Okpus Brown Braye\n* Amadi Samuel\n* Brown Okpus\n* Odeyemi Ebenezer\n* Onomado Good luck (C)\n* Olalere Oluwasegun\n* Ubido Julius\n* Upele Charles\n* Daniel A\n* Ogar David\n* Onome Onotefe\n* Williams Sunday\n* Abah John\n* Omodiagbe Victory\n* Ocheayi Richards\n* Ridwan Agbabiyaka\n* Jonah Abutu\n* Wisdom J\n* Uro ibor\n* Iteye Jimmy\n* Okon Eta\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n\n\n[[Category:Football clubs in Nigeria]]\n[[Category:Delta State]]\n[